  "prompt": "What are some good figure skating songs?",
  "response": "Figure skating programs often feature music with strong emotional resonance, a clear rhythm, and dynamic changes to match the skater's movements and choreography. Here are some popular and effective songs and pieces used in figure skating:\n\n### Classical and Orchestral\n1. **\"Carmen\" by Georges Bizet**\n2. **\"Swan Lake\" by Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky**\n3. **\"Romeo and Juliet\" by Sergei Prokofiev**\n4. **\"Bol\u00e9ro\" by Maurice Ravel**\n5. **\"The Four Seasons\" by Antonio Vivaldi**\n6. **\"Moonlight Sonata\" by Ludwig van Beethoven**\n7. **\"Adagio for Strings\" by Samuel Barber**\n\n### Contemporary and Popular\n1. **\"Hallelujah\" by Leonard Cohen**\n2. **\"A Sky Full of Stars\" by Coldplay**\n3. **\"Shape of You\" by Ed Sheeran**\n4. **\"You Raise Me Up\" by Secret Garden**\n5. **\"Let It Go\" from *Frozen*** (Idina Menzel)\n6. **\"River Flows in You\" by Yiruma**\n7. **\"Time to Say Goodbye\" by Andrea Bocelli and Sarah Brightman**\n\n### Soundtracks and Thematic Pieces\n1. **\"Pirates of the Caribbean\" Soundtrack (Hans Zimmer)**\n2. **\"Gladiator\" Soundtrack (Hans Zimmer)**\n3. **\"The Phantom of the Opera\" by Andrew Lloyd Webber**\n4. **\"Titanic\" Soundtrack (James Horner)**\n5. **\"The Nutcracker\" by Pyotr Ilyich Tchaikovsky**\n\n### Jazz and Swing\n1. **\"Feeling Good\" by Michael Bubl\u00e9**\n2. **\"Sing, Sing, Sing\" by Benny Goodman**\n3. **\"Fly Me to the Moon\" by Frank Sinatra**\n\n### Emotional Ballads\n1. **\"My Heart Will Go On\" by Celine Dion**\n2. **\"I Will Always Love You\" by Whitney Houston**\n3. **\"Someone Like You\" by Adele**\n\n### Dramatic and Powerful\n1. **\"O Fortuna\" from *Carmina Burana* by Carl Orff**\n2. **\"Requiem\" by Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart**\n3. **\"Danse Macabre\" by Camille Saint-Sa\u00ebns**\n\n### Latin and World Music\n1. **\"Bamboleo\" by Gipsy Kings**\n2. **\"Malague\u00f1a\" by Ernesto Lecuona**\n3. **\"Tango de Roxanne\" from *Moulin Rouge***\n\nWhen choosing a song for figure skating, it\u2019s important to consider the skater\u2019s style, strengths, and the program\u2019s theme. The music should inspire the choreography and complement the skater\u2019s performance.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
